               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Samāʿtāt, Vitae of Saints and Martyrs (fols. 1ra-55vb) [cp.
                     Orient 691 (15th cent.) fols. 1a-218b (WrBriMus 163-63, no. 255); Orient 686,
                     fol. 58a-b (WrBriMus 167, no. 257/14); EMML no. 1833 (14th cent.) fols. 1a-170b
                     (EMML V, 302-5)]
 I-1) Manifestation of the Prophet Habakkuk (ʿƎnbaqom) at
                     Qärṭäsa (for the 3rd of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 1ra-11va, 18ra-vb, 20ra-vb, 43ra-vb),
                     incomplete [s. C. CONTI ROSSINI, “La leggenda di Habacuch nella versione
                     etiopica”, in: Scritti etiopici raccolti da C. Conti Rossini, Roma 1945,
                     17-40]
 I-2) Commemoration of Eleazar (ʾƎlʿazar) the son of Aron (for the
                     3rd of Ḫǝdār) (fol. 11va-b)
 I-3) Homily by Theophilus of Alexandria on the
                     blessed Virgin Mary for the 6th of Ḫǝdār (fols. 11vb-17vb, 19ra-31vb),
                     incomplete [cp. C. CONTI ROSSINI, “Il discorso su monte Coscam attribuito a
                     Teofilo d’Alessandria nella versione etiopica”, RANLmor ser. 5, 21, 1912,
                     395-471; CANT no. 56] 
 I-4) Taʾammǝra Giyorgis “Miracles of George”:
                     Introduction and 4 miracles (for the 7th of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 33ra-40vb),
                     incomplete
 I-5) Homily on the Archangel Michael by Severus the patriarch
                     of Antioch (for the 12th of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 41ra-vb, 55ra-va), incomplete
                     I-6) Homily on the 24 Elders (Heavenly Priests) by Severus the Patriarch of
                     Antioch, “an admonition to priests” (for the 24th of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 42ra-vb,
                     45ra-46vb, 48ra-b, 56ra-vb), incomplete
 I-7) Martyrdom of Jacob the
                     Persian (Yāʿqob Gǝmud) (for the 27th of Ḫǝdār) (fol. 48rb-vb), incomplete
                     I-8) Passio of Cosmas and Damianus (for the 22nd of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 49ra-vb,
                     51ra-54vb), incomplete
 I-9) History of ʾAskänafǝr (ʾAksänafǝr) a judge of
                     Rome written by Epiphanius of Cyprus (for the 13th of Ḫǝdār) (fols. 50ra-vb,
                     55va-b), incomplete.
 
 Texts on fols. 44 and 47 have not been
                     identified.</summary>
