                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red</seg>
                        <date>15th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Incipits and heading of the texts; Ethiopic
                           numerals; caesura signs; paragraph signs (on the left side of columns);
                           elements of the punctuation signs.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The quality of the handwriting remains
                        the same throughout the Ms. Tall and angular letters; the body of several
                        letters is triangular (e.g.: ዐ, ለ, መ); the marker of the sixth order of ጰ is
                        attached to the left side of the main body; the vowel marker of the seventh
                        order of ለ is attached directly at the body of the letter, without the
                        connecting line; the seventh order marker of ተ is attached directly at the
                        crossing stroke of bar; the seventh order of ቀ is directly attached at the
                        loops; the loops of መ are not separated; the numbers in the text headings
                        and notes in the upper margin of the fols. are always written without dashes
                        above and below (but with dashes within the text); the loops of the number
                        two are not separated and have the same width (e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>, 11va,
                        etc.).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
